## Frequently Asked Questions

<div class="faq-section">
  <div class="faq-item">
    <h3>How long does tank insulation take?</h3>
    <p>Most tanks can be insulated in one day. Larger tanks or multiple tank projects may take 2-3 days. The foam cures quickly, and tanks can be used immediately after application.</p>
  </div>
  
  <div class="faq-item">
    <h3>Will the insulation affect water quality?</h3>
    <p>No. Once cured, closed-cell spray foam is completely inert and safe for potable water applications. It actually improves water quality by reducing temperature and algae growth.</p>
  </div>
  
  <div class="faq-item">
    <h3>How long does tank insulation last?</h3>
    <p>With proper UV coating, tank insulation lasts 25+ years in Arizona conditions. It's a one-time investment that pays dividends for decades.</p>
  </div>
  
  <div class="faq-item">
    <h3>Can you insulate tanks that are currently in use?</h3>
    <p>Yes! We can insulate tanks without draining them. The exterior application doesn't affect the water inside, minimizing disruption to your operations.</p>
  </div>
